 this letter. And please do put it in your future contracts with them that I have to be consuited about cover designs. The one they put on NABOKOV'S DOZEN was pretty bad and insulting, but this one is the limit.





Cordially yours,

Vladimir Nabokov





TO: GERMANO FACETTI1

CC, 1 p.





Montreux, April 13, 1963

